ited States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{main|List of United States women's national soccer team matches}}\n\n== 1980s ==\nThe team was founded in 1985, and played 31 matched before the end of the decade.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ussoccerhistory.org/usnt-results/uswnt-results/uswnt-results-1985-1989/|title=USWNT Results, 1985-1989|date=2019-02-28|website=Society for American Soccer History|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-08}}</ref>\n\n=== [[1985 United States women's national soccer team|1985]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Competition\n!Location\n!Opponent\n!Result\n!US scorers\n|-\n|August 18, 1985\n|[[Mundialito (women)|Mundialito Tournament]]\n|[[Jesolo, Italy]]\n|[[Italy women's national football team|Italy]]\n|0\u20131\n|n/a\n|-\n|August 21, 1985\n|Mundialito\n|Jesolo, Italy\n|[[Denmark women's national football team|Denmark]]\n|2\u20132\n|[[Michelle Akers]], [[Emily Pickering]]\n|-\n|August 23, 1985\n|Mundialito\n|[[Caorle, Italy]]\n|[[England women's national football team|England]]\n|1\u20133\n|[[Michelle Akers]]\n|-\n|August 24, 1985\n|Mundialito\n|Jesolo, Italy\n|[[Denmark women's national football team|Denmark]]\n|0\u20131\n|n/a\n|}<br />\n\n=== 1986 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Competition\n!Location\n!Opponent\n!Result\n!US scorers\n|-\n|July 7, 1986\n|Friendly\n|[[Blaine, Minnesota|Blaine, MN]]\n|[[Canada women's national soccer team|Canada]]\n|2\u20130\n|[[Marcia McDermott]], [[Joan Dunlap-Seivold|Joan Dunlap]]\n|-\n|July 9, 1986\n|Friendly\n|Blaine, MN\n|Canada\n|1\u20132\n|[[Lisa Gmitter-Pittaro|Lisa Gmitter]]\n|-\n|July 9, 1986\n|Friendly\n|Blaine, MN\n|Canada\n|3\u20130\n|[[April Heinrichs]] (2), [[Marcia McDermott]]\n|-\n|July 20, 1986\n|[[Mundialito (women)|Mundialito]]\n|[[Jesolo, Italy]]\n|[[China women's national football team|China]]\n|2\u20131\n|[[April Heinrichs]], [[Marcia McDermott]]\n|-\n|July 22, 1986\n|Mundialito\n|Jesolo, Italy\n|[[Brazil women's national football 